<!-- HOW WE DO IT -->
<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-primary tracking-tighter mb-4">How We Do It</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary max-w-3xl mb-10">Our six-step process ensures a durable, professional finish that lasts for years. Good ventilation is required during the spraying process.</p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">1</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Deep Clean &amp; Degrease</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">Every tile surface is thoroughly cleaned and degreased to remove soap scum, body oils, mineral deposits, and any contaminants that could prevent the coating from bonding properly.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">2</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Sand &amp; Etch Surface</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">The tile surface is sanded and etched to create a mechanical key for the coating to grip. This step is critical for long-term adhesion &mdash; it's what separates a professional job from a DIY paint job that peels.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">3</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Mask &amp; Protect</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">All fixtures, fittings, floors, ceilings, and adjacent surfaces are carefully masked with protective sheeting and tape. We protect everything that isn't being resurfaced.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">4</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Apply Bonding Primer</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">A specialist bonding primer is applied to the prepared tile surface. This creates a chemical bond between the existing tile and the topcoat, ensuring the finish stays put for years.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">5</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Spray Professional Coating</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">Multiple coats of a professional two-part coating are sprayed in your chosen colour. Spraying (rather than rolling) gives an even, smooth, factory-like finish with no brush marks or texture.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface-container-low rounded-xl p-6 reveal">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold mb-4">6</div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-primary text-sm mb-2">Cure &amp; Inspect</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-secondary leading-relaxed">The coating cures to a hard, durable finish. We inspect every surface for consistency and coverage. The bathroom should be kept dry for 48 hours to allow full curing before normal use.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

